'''Bonnie Shade''' is a historic [[Plantation house in the Southern United States|plantation house]] located at [[Florence, South Carolina|Florence]], [[Florence County, South Carolina]].  It was built in 1854, and is a mid-19th century [[Greek Revival architecture|Greek Revival]] style raised cottage.  It features corner pilasters and free-standing columns supporting the pediment and [[portico]].<ref name = nrhpinv>{{Cite web | author = Julie Burr and Pete Rogers | title =Bonnie Shade | work = National Register of Historic Places - Nomination and Inventory | date = March 1978| url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721002/S10817721002.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref><ref name = scdah>{{Cite web | title = Bonnie Shade, Florence County (1439 Cherokee Rd., Florence) | work = National Register Properties in South Carolina | publisher = South Carolina Department of Archives and History  | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721002/index.htm | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1978.<ref name = nris/>

